          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12715724/comment/17936782",
            "id": "17936782",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=frensjan",
              "name": "frensjan",
              "key": "frensjan",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=frensjan&avatarId=52398",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=frensjan&avatarId=52398",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=frensjan&avatarId=52398",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=frensjan&avatarId=52398"
              },
              "displayName": "Frens Jan Rumph",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Europe/Berlin"
            },
            "body": "This seems like a long standing issue. I probably don't have a clear view on whether it addresses any or all of the concerns related to this issue. I ran ran into the limitation of POST requests being rejected by the YARN server web proxy in combination with the Flink UI.\r\n\r\nI have a patch in place that extends the support for GET and PUT with POST: [https://github.com/apache/hadoop/compare/trunk...frensjan:hadoop:yarn-proxy-post?expand=1]. I haven't contributed to Hadoop before; I'd appreciate any advise on getting this to work. Either for getting the changes merged in Hadoop or pointing me in another direction.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=frensjan",
              "name": "frensjan",
              "key": "frensjan",
